%description
Regularization by Denoising uses a denoising engine to solve many image
reconstruction ill-posed inverse problems. This is a R implementation of
the algorithm developed by Romano et.al. (2016) <arXiv:1611.02862>.
Currently, only the gradient descent optimization framework is
implemented. Also, only the median filter is implemented as a denoiser
engine. However, (almost) any denoiser engine can be plugged in. There are
currently available 3 reconstruction tasks: denoise, deblur and
super-resolution. And again, any other task can be easily plugged into the
main function 'RED'.

